---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Home">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 pt-24 pb-12">
    <div class="animate-in">
      <h1 class="text-5xl font-medium tracking-tight leading-tight mb-6" style="line-height:1.1">
        Figma x Contra
        <br />Makeathon Analysis
      </h1>
    </div>
    <p class="text-lg text-muted-foreground max-w-2xl leading-relaxed mb-8 animate-in animate-in-delay-1" style="line-height:1.7">
      Three editions. Thousands of participants. One question: what separates
      winners from the crowd? We scraped real Contra data to find out.
    </p>
    <div class="flex gap-4 animate-in animate-in-delay-2">
      <a href="/report" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 rounded-xl text-sm font-medium transition-all duration-200" style="background: #BA7517; color: #FFFFFF;">
        Read the Full Report
      </a>
      <a href="/charts" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 rounded-xl border border-border text-foreground text-sm font-medium hover:border-foreground transition-all duration-200">
        Explore Charts
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Winning Formula -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 pb-12">
    <div class="rounded-2xl p-8 animate-in animate-in-delay-3" style="background: #BA751710; border: 2px solid #BA751740;">
      <div class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-6" style="color:#BA7517">The Formula — derived from 4,212 posts across 3 editions</div>

      <div class="text-lg font-semibold text-foreground mb-6">To win =</div>

      <div class="space-y-4 pl-4 border-l-2" style="border-color:#BA7517">

        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <span class="text-xl font-bold shrink-0 w-6 text-center mt-0.5" style="color:#1D9E75">①</span>
          <div>
            <div class="font-semibold text-foreground">An interaction design that surprises people</div>
            <div class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mt-0.5">Not a feature. Not a screen. A moment that makes someone think "how did they do that?"</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <span class="text-xl font-bold shrink-0 w-6 text-center mt-0.5" style="color:#BA7517">×</span>
          <div>
            <div class="font-semibold text-foreground">A working video that proves it</div>
            <div class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mt-0.5">40–90% of winners included a demo video vs 7–56% of non-winners. Screenshots don't move. Ideas need proof.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <span class="text-xl font-bold shrink-0 w-6 text-center mt-0.5" style="color:#BA7517">+</span>
          <div>
            <div class="font-semibold text-foreground">Post before the crowd does</div>
            <div class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mt-0.5">In the 8-day Sep 2025 window, winners posted 0.8 days earlier on average. Early posts compound engagement while others are still designing.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <span class="text-xl font-bold shrink-0 w-6 text-center mt-0.5" style="color:#BA7517">+</span>
          <div>
            <div class="font-semibold text-foreground">Something people actually want to share</div>
            <div class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mt-0.5">Winners averaged 54.4 likes vs 7.1 for non-winners. That gap isn't luck — it's the community recognizing work worth spreading.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <div class="mt-6 pt-5 border-t border-border text-sm text-muted-foreground">
        The judges don't comment on posts before announcing winners. They review externally.
        <strong class="text-foreground"> You cannot game the selection — only the quality of the work.</strong>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 pb-20">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4 mb-20">
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border p-6 bg-card card-hover animate-in animate-in-delay-1">
        <div class="text-4xl font-medium text-amber-400 mb-1 stat-number" style="color:#BA7517; line-height:1.1">3,303</div>
        <div class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Unique Creators Posted</div>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border p-6 bg-card card-hover animate-in animate-in-delay-2">
        <div class="text-4xl font-medium mb-1 stat-number" style="color:#BA7517; line-height:1.1">3</div>
        <div class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Makeathon Editions</div>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border p-6 bg-card card-hover animate-in animate-in-delay-3">
        <div class="text-4xl font-medium mb-1 stat-number" style="color:#BA7517; line-height:1.1">6,030</div>
        <div class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Posts Scraped</div>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border p-6 bg-card card-hover animate-in animate-in-delay-4">
        <div class="text-4xl font-medium mb-1 stat-number" style="color:#BA7517; line-height:1.1">$300K</div>
        <div class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Total Prize Pool</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium mb-2 animate-in" style="line-height:1.2">What the Data Shows</h2>
    <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-8 animate-in animate-in-delay-1" style="line-height:1.7">4,219 in-window posts analyzed. Real engagement data. Real winners. Three editions.</p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border p-6 bg-card card-hover animate-in animate-in-delay-1">
        <h3 class="font-medium mb-2">7.7× Engagement Gap</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground" style="line-height:1.7">
          Winners averaged <strong class="text-foreground font-medium">54.4 likes</strong> vs <strong class="text-foreground font-medium">7.1</strong> for non-winners across all three editions.
          High engagement and winning co-occur because quality drives both.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border p-6 bg-card card-hover animate-in animate-in-delay-2">
        <h3 class="font-medium mb-2">Video is the Strongest Signal</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground" style="line-height:1.7">
          40–90% of winners included a video demo vs only 7–56% of non-winners.
          A working demo shows the interaction is real and drives shares.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border p-6 bg-card card-hover animate-in animate-in-delay-3">
        <h3 class="font-medium mb-2">Cara Ellis Had 217 Likes</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground" style="line-height:1.7">
          The Sep 2025 winner's Web Poetry post was the <strong class="text-foreground font-medium">3rd most-liked</strong> post in the entire 8-day contest window. Winning and community popularity aligned.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border p-6 bg-card card-hover animate-in animate-in-delay-4">
        <h3 class="font-medium mb-2">Lee Black Won Twice</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground" style="line-height:1.7">
          The only two-time winner: <strong class="text-foreground font-medium">Airwwave</strong> (March 2026)
          and <strong class="text-foreground font-medium">Connected Earth</strong> (Config 2026).
          Entirely different projects, same consistent quality.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 rounded-2xl border border-border p-6 bg-card animate-in">
      <h3 class="font-medium mb-2">Methodology Note</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground" style="line-height:1.7">
        6,030 posts scraped via authenticated Contra GraphQL API from within the browser
        (session auth bypassed the 2,020-result anonymous cap). Two sort passes per tag
        (ENGAGEMENT + CREATED_AT). Filtered to 4,219 in-window posts across all 3 editions.
        Config 2026 winners announced at Config, June 23, 2026. Full methodology in the report.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
